<div class="xar-mod-head">
  <span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>JpGraph Administration</xar:mlstring></span>
</div>
<div id="notsogoodbutok" class="xar-mod-body">
  <!-- include a standard tabbed admin menu via include file in the xartemplates/include folder -->
  <xar:template type="module" module="jpgraph" file="admin-menu" />
  <img src="#xarTplGetImage('JpGraph_Logo.png','jpgraph')#" class="xar-module-icon" alt="official icon" width="152" height="107" />

  <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <p>
    <em><xar:mlstring>JpGraph is a wrapper module for the JpGraph library.</xar:mlstring></em>
    <xar:mlstring>The JpGraph library is capable of serving you with various nice graphs including:</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Single or multiple line plots.</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Single or multiple bar plots.</xar:mlstring></li>

  </ol>
  <p><xar:mlstring>This module provides you with:</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>A nice location for the classes.</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Templates with standard style classes, layouts and template requirements to meet Xaraya Block Layout coding standards.</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>A property that will present you with the basic plot types.</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li>
      <xar:mlstring>For more detailed info, look in the templates (e.g. xartemplates//admin-new.xd) in this module.</xar:mlstring>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <p>
  <xar:mlstring>Get the JpGraph library from the website at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.aditus.nu/jpgraph/jpdownload.php">http://www.aditus.nu/jpgraph/jpdownload.php</a><br />
  <xar:mlstring>Unzip the files. Copy the files from /src to /xarincludes/jpgraph2/ and the files from /docs to /xardocs/. The, copy the config file from xarincludes over to the jpgraph2 directory.</xar:mlstring>
  <br />
  <xar:mlstring>Run the test suit to see what goes ok on your system. Set any options in modifyconfig and optionally the others in the jpg-config.inc.php file in xarincludes/jpgraph2.</xar:mlstring>
  </p>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Tools</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="modules/jpgraph/xarincludes/jpgraph2/Examples/testsuit.php"><xar:mlstring>Test suit</xar:mlstring></a></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>jpgraph</xar:mlstring></li>
  </ul>


  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Dynamic Data Properties</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>JpGraph -- Provides some basic plots created by the jpgraph code.</xar:mlstring></li>

  </ul>

  <h3>
    <xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring>
  </h3>
  <p>
    <xar:mlstring>Further information on the JpGraph module can be found at</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>JpGraph Extension page at</xar:mlstring> <a title="#xarML('Example Module - Xaraya Extension 36')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/36.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
      <xar:mlstring> Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
    </li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation on JpGraph found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/keywords/jpgraph/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on JpGraph')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="xar-sub">
    <strong>&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>JpGraph Module - Overview</xar:mlstring></strong><br />&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>Version</xar:mlstring> 1.0.1&nbsp; 2006-11-17
